[SN]TITLE[SN]
Peterborough United 4-0 Doncaster Rovers

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Peterborough United gave former manager Darren Ferguson an unwelcome return to London Road as they thrashed Doncaster Rovers in League One.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gaby Zakuani nodded Erhun Oztumer's corner home to take the lead, before Oztumer then tapped in a second.
Callum Elder found a third for Posh two minutes after the break before Conor Washington's drive secured victory.
Rovers came close to a consolation through Andy Butler but Michael Bostick cleared his header off the line.
